**[Bioinformatics](/Bioinformatics)**

*   **Databases**
    *   Sequence databases: [GenBank](/GenBank), [European Nucleotide Archive](/European_Nucleotide_Archive), [DNA Data Bank of Japan](/DNA_Data_Bank_of_Japan) and [China National GeneBank](/China_National_GeneBank). (The foundational archives of genetic information.)
    *   Secondary databases: [UniProt](/UniProt), a comprehensive repository of protein sequences, encompassing the older [Swiss-Prot](/UniProt), [TrEMBL](/UniProt), and [Protein Information Resource](/Protein_Information_Resource). (Consolidation, a recurring theme.)
    *   Other databases: [BioNumbers](/BioNumbers), [Protein Data Bank](/Protein_Data_Bank), [Ensembl](/Ensembl_genome_database_project), [InterPro](/InterPro), [KEGG](/KEGG), and [Gene Ontology](/Gene_ontology). (A diverse landscape of biological data.)
    *   Specialised genomic databases: [BOLD](/Barcode_of_Life_Data_System), [Saccharomyces Genome Database](/Saccharomyces_Genome_Database), [FlyBase](/FlyBase), [VectorBase](/VectorBase), [WormBase](/WormBase), [Rat Genome Database](/Rat_Genome_Database), [PHI-base](/PHI-base), [The Arabidopsis Information Resource](/The_Arabidopsis_Information_Resource), [GISAID](/GISAID), and [Zebrafish Information Network](/Zebrafish_Information_Network). (Targeted repositories for specific organisms and fields.)

